<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xml:lang="en"><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="4.3.3">Jekyll</generator><link href="https://trandangtrungduc.github.io/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml"/><link href="https://trandangtrungduc.github.io/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" hreflang="en"/><updated>2026-03-29T09:31:07+00:00</updated><id>https://trandangtrungduc.github.io/feed.xml</id><title type="html">blank</title><subtitle>A simple, whitespace theme for academics. Based on [*folio](https://github.com/bogoli/-folio) design. </subtitle><entry><title type="html">CronyClaw</title><link href="https://trandangtrungduc.github.io/blog/2026/CronyClaw/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="CronyClaw"/><published>2026-03-27T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2026-03-27T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://trandangtrungduc.github.io/blog/2026/CronyClaw</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://trandangtrungduc.github.io/blog/2026/CronyClaw/"><![CDATA[<p>This project is a <em>Vibe Coding Web &amp; Desktop Application</em> built with <strong>TypeScript</strong>, featuring a <strong>Python backend</strong> and <strong>Electron</strong> for the desktop experience.</p> <p>It extends the original <a href="https://github.com/Open-LLM-VTuber/Open-LLM-VTuber">OpenLLM Vtuber</a> project to create an interactive <strong>Live2D character</strong> capable of real-time communication, voice cloning, emotional expression, and screen awareness.</p> <p>The system integrates multiple LLM and VLM technologies, including <strong>Qwen</strong>, <strong>OpenAI</strong>, <strong>Gemini</strong>, <strong>Ollama</strong>, <strong>IndexTTS</strong>, and <strong>Edge TTS</strong>,… enabling rich multimodal interaction between the user and the AI character.</p> <p>Additionally, it supports seamless integration with <a href="https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw">OpenClaw</a>, allowing users to manage tasks (e.g., starting, completing) through a unified interface. Users can interact via text messages or <strong>ASR</strong> using their voice, while the AI can combine different <strong>skills</strong> to execute tasks efficiently through OpenClaw.</p> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0 d-flex justify-content-center"> <figure> <video src="/assets/video/cronyclaw_1.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" autoplay="" controls=""/> </figure> </div> <p>Check <a href="https://github.com/trandangtrungduc/CronyClaw">here</a> for details.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="vibe-coding-project"/><category term="vibe-coding"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[project videos]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">AI Art Portal for Game Development</title><link href="https://trandangtrungduc.github.io/blog/2026/AI-art-portal-game-development/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="AI Art Portal for Game Development"/><published>2026-02-02T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2026-02-02T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://trandangtrungduc.github.io/blog/2026/AI-art-portal-game-development</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://trandangtrungduc.github.io/blog/2026/AI-art-portal-game-development/"><![CDATA[<p>This project is a <em>Vibe Coding Web Application</em> built with <strong>TypeScript</strong> on the frontend and <strong>Python</strong> on the backend.</p> <p>It integrates advanced models and tools such as <strong>Nano Banana</strong>, <strong>Qwen Editing</strong>, and <strong>Wan 2.6</strong> to streamline AI-powered content creation. The platform serves as a centralized repository of standardized AI workflows for generating art and design assets, including both images and videos.</p> <p>Additionally, the system supports <strong>MCP (Model Context Protocol)</strong>, enabling seamless integration with tools like <strong>Claude</strong> and <strong>Cursor</strong>. This makes it easier to automate, reuse, and scale creative pipelines for rapid production and experimentation.</p> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0 d-flex justify-content-center"> <figure> <video src="/assets/video/AI_portal_apps.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" autoplay="" controls=""/> </figure> </div> <p>Check <a href="https://github.com/trandangtrungduc/AIArtPortalForGameDevelopment">here</a> for details.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="vibe-coding-project"/><category term="vibe-coding"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[project videos]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">AI Game Warehouse Application</title><link href="https://trandangtrungduc.github.io/blog/2025/AI-game-warehouse/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="AI Game Warehouse Application"/><published>2025-12-07T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2025-12-07T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://trandangtrungduc.github.io/blog/2025/AI-game-warehouse</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://trandangtrungduc.github.io/blog/2025/AI-game-warehouse/"><![CDATA[<p>This project is a <em>Vibe Coding Web Application</em> built with <strong>TypeScript</strong>, powered by <strong>Google Gemini</strong>.</p> <p>It serves as a repository of AI-generated games, where each application is a standalone interactive experience that can be played directly in the browser. Users can also interact with AI in real time within each game, creating dynamic and engaging gameplay.</p> <p>The platform is designed for storing game prototypes and enabling quick demos, making it ideal for rapid experimentation, showcasing ideas, and iterating on AI-driven game concepts.</p> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0 d-flex justify-content-center"> <figure> <video src="/assets/video/AI_game_warehouse_1.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" autoplay="" controls=""/> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0 d-flex justify-content-center"> <figure> <video src="/assets/video/AI_game_warehouse_2.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" autoplay="" controls=""/> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0 d-flex justify-content-center"> <figure> <video src="/assets/video/AI_game_warehouse_3.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" autoplay="" controls=""/> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0 d-flex justify-content-center"> <figure> <video src="/assets/video/AI_game_warehouse_4.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" autoplay="" controls=""/> </figure> </div> <p>Check <a href="https://github.com/trandangtrungduc/AIGameWarehouseApplication">here</a> for details.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="vibe-coding-project"/><category term="vibe-coding"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[project videos]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">AI Character in Game</title><link href="https://trandangtrungduc.github.io/blog/2025/AI-character-in-game/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="AI Character in Game"/><published>2025-10-25T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2025-10-25T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://trandangtrungduc.github.io/blog/2025/AI-character-in-game</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://trandangtrungduc.github.io/blog/2025/AI-character-in-game/"><![CDATA[<p>This project is part of a Vibe Coding Game series, developed using the <strong>Pygame</strong>. The core gameplay is inspired by the original <a href="https://www.codingwithruss.com/gamepage/Shooter/">Shooter</a> game, with enhancements focused on integrating AI-driven interactions.</p> <p>The in-game 2D AI character (design, generation and animation) is generated using the <a href="https://www.pixellab.ai/">PixelLab platform</a>, bringing a unique visual identity to the experience. Additionally, the project leverages advanced language and speech capabilities powered by <strong>Qwen</strong> from Alibaba, incorporating both LLM (language understanding) and TTS (text-to-speech) models to create a more immersive and dynamic gameplay experience.</p> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0 d-flex justify-content-center"> <figure> <video src="/assets/video/AI_character_2D_game_1.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" autoplay="" controls=""/> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0 d-flex justify-content-center"> <figure> <video src="/assets/video/AI_character_2D_game_2.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" autoplay="" controls=""/> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0 d-flex justify-content-center"> <figure> <video src="/assets/video/AI_character_2D_game_3.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" autoplay="" controls=""/> </figure> </div> <p>The in-game 3D AI character (design, generation and animation) is generated using the <a href="https://3d.hunyuanglobal.com/">Hunyuan 3D platform</a> from Tencent. The core gameplay is inspired by the original <a href="https://github.com/wass08/r3f-playroom-multiplayer-shooter-game">Multiplayer Shooter Game</a>.</p> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0 d-flex justify-content-center"> <figure> <video src="/assets/video/AI_character_3D_game.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" autoplay="" controls=""/> </figure> </div> <p>Check <a href="https://github.com/trandangtrungduc/AICharacterInGame">here</a> for details.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="vibe-coding-project"/><category term="vibe-coding"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[project videos]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Fast Game Asset Generation Application</title><link href="https://trandangtrungduc.github.io/blog/2025/fast-game-asset-generation-app/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Fast Game Asset Generation Application"/><published>2025-07-14T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2025-07-14T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://trandangtrungduc.github.io/blog/2025/fast-game-asset-generation-app</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://trandangtrungduc.github.io/blog/2025/fast-game-asset-generation-app/"><![CDATA[<p>This project is a Vibe Coding Web Application built with <strong>TypeScript</strong> on the frontend and <strong>Python</strong> on the backend, designed for ultra-fast AI image generation.</p> <p>It leverages state-of-the-art models such as <a href="https://github.com/NVlabs/Sana">Sana</a>, capable of generating images in under <strong>0.2 seconds per image</strong>, and <a href="https://github.com/FoundationVision/Infinity">Infinity</a> for high-quality and scalable generation.</p> <p>The system supports advanced features including <strong>ControlNet</strong> for guided image generation, <strong>Inpainting</strong> for precise image editing, and <strong>custom LoRA training</strong> to adapt and personalize image styles. This enables users to quickly generate, refine, and customize visuals with high performance and flexibility.</p> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0 d-flex justify-content-center"> <figure> <video src="/assets/video/fast_image_generation.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" autoplay="" controls=""/> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0 d-flex justify-content-center"> <figure> <video src="/assets/video/fast_sticker_generation.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" autoplay="" controls=""/> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0 d-flex justify-content-center"> <figure> <video src="/assets/video/fast_texture_generation.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" autoplay="" controls=""/> </figure> </div> <p>Check <a href="https://github.com/trandangtrungduc/FastGameAssetGenerationApp">here</a> for details.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="vibe-coding-project"/><category term="vibe-coding"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[project videos]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Multi-scale Twin-attention for 3D Instance Segmentation</title><link href="https://trandangtrungduc.github.io/blog/2024/3d-instance_segmentation/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Multi-scale Twin-attention for 3D Instance Segmentation"/><published>2024-07-21T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2024-07-21T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://trandangtrungduc.github.io/blog/2024/3d-instance_segmentation</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://trandangtrungduc.github.io/blog/2024/3d-instance_segmentation/"><![CDATA[<p>Visualize results on validation set of <a href="http://www.scan-net.org/">ScanNetv2</a> dataset.</p> <div class="caption"> Top row: from left to right are Input Point Cloud, High-scale Superpoint, Low-scale Superpoint and Ground-truth respectively </div> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/msta3d/Figure_6_4_input.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/msta3d/Figure_6_4_high_scale.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/msta3d/Figure_6_4_low_scale.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/msta3d/Figure_6_4_ground_truth.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/msta3d/Figure_6_4_ISBNet.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/msta3d/Figure_6_4_SPFormer.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/msta3d/Figure_6_4_MAFT.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/msta3d/Figure_6_4_Ours.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="caption"> Bottom row: from left to right are <a href="https://github.com/VinAIResearch/ISBNet">ISBNet</a>, <a href="https://github.com/sunjiahao1999/SPFormer">SPFormer</a>, <a href="https://github.com/dvlab-research/Mask-Attention-Free-Transformer">MAFT</a> and MSTA3D respectively </div> <p>Other examples</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <div class="slideshow-container"> <div class="mySlides"> <div class="numbertext">1 / 4</div> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/msta3d/Figure_7_ISBNet.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> <div class="text">ISBNet</div> </div> <div class="mySlides"> <div class="numbertext">2 / 4</div> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/msta3d/Figure_7_SPFormer.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> <div class="text">SPFormer</div> </div> <div class="mySlides"> <div class="numbertext">3 / 4</div> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/msta3d/Figure_7_MAFT.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> <div class="text">MAFT</div> </div> <div class="mySlides"> <div class="numbertext">4 / 4</div> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/msta3d/Figure_7_Ours.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> <div class="text">MSTA3D</div> </div> <a class="prev" onclick="plusSlides(-1)">&#10094;</a> <a class="next" onclick="plusSlides(1)">&#10095;</a> </div> <div style="text-align:center"> <span class="dot" onclick="currentSlide(1)"></span> <span class="dot" onclick="currentSlide(2)"></span> <span class="dot" onclick="currentSlide(3)"></span> <span class="dot" onclick="currentSlide(4)"></span> </div> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <div class="img-comp-container"> <div class="img-comp-img"> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/msta3d/Figure_6_3_input.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="300" height="200" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="img-comp-img img-comp-overlay"> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/msta3d/Figure_6_3_Ours.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="300" height="200" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> </div> </div> <style>*{box-siz